<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-2820] System tests: log level is no longer propagating from service classes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-2820</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Many system test service classes specify a log level which should be reflected in the log4j output of the corresponding kafka tools etc.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, at least some these log levels are no longer propagating, which makes tests much harder to debug after they have run.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;E.g. KafkaService specifies a DEBUG log level, but all collected log output from brokers is at INFO level or above.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
